refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arrayfstat resourcehandle
Gathers the statistics of the file opened by the file pointer handle. This function is similar to the stat function except that it operates on an open file pointer instead of a filename.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns an array with the statistics of the file; the format of the array
 is described in detail on the stat manual page.

  &reftitle.examples;



    fstat example


<?php

// open a file
$fp = fopen("/etc/passwd", "r");

// gather statistics
$fstat = fstat($fp);

// close the file
fclose($fp);

// print only the associative part
print_r(array_slice($fstat, 13));

?>


